column3: Lali-yet another recording device has arrived-ho. Whatever Konogg's up to, as long as he keeps sending these, we can assume he's safe and well. Anyway, here you go.
Um, Chief? Can I speak with you for a moment?
It's Glagg. I ran into him just now, and he was behaving oddly...
Just when you think he's angry, he suddenly bursts into tears. And the next thing you know, he's talking with you like you're an old friend.
Ah, that... He's been that way since the meeting.
But I'll sort him out, so don't worry. Thanks for bringing me word, and let me know if you notice anything else.
It seems Glagg's condition isn't common knowledge yet. But it's only a matter of time if it continues to worsen, like it seems to be doing.
Sorry, I'm saying all of this out loud, but it's not your problem to deal with. Just stay focused on the rebuilding─that's how you'll best help us.
You obtain a message from Konogg.

The message can be viewed in your <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Portable Archive<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>, which is available under Collection in the Duty section of the main menu.
